---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';

---

<BlogLayout title="About" bg="#dbeafe">

  <canvas id="canvas-0" class="about-canvas"></canvas>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Welcome to my little corner of the internet 👋  
    This space exists purely because I wanted a place to think out loud. 
    It’s a collection of my thoughts, experiences, experiments, and the occasional 
    over-analysis of things I probably didn’t need to over-analyze. 
  </p> 

  <p class="mb-4">
    I also built my own very basic 3D rendering engine to generate the simple 
    3D models I designed in Tinkercad. If that sounds even remotely interesting 
    (or confusing), head over to the <strong>Projects</strong> page — 
    that’s where I document the technical rabbit holes I willingly jump into.
  </p>
  
  <p class="mb-4">
    This isn’t a polished publication. It’s not a startup blog. 
    It’s not a productivity newsletter.  
    It’s just me, writing about things I love, technology, ideas, One piece,
    and whatever else feels worth documenting.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    There’s no posting schedule, no content strategy, and absolutely no guarantee 
    of professionalism. Just curiosity and the occasional burst of motivation.
  </p>

  <script>
    import { Renderer3D } from "../../scripts/rendering.js";
    import { loadMeshJSON } from "../../scripts/mesh.js";
  
    window.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", async () => {
      try {
        const mesh = await loadMeshJSON('/welcome.json');
        const FPS = 15;
        const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas-0');
        if(!canvas) return;
          const canvasId = canvas.id;
          const renderer = new Renderer3D('canvas-0');
          
          let angle = 0;
          let uprightAngle = -Math.PI / 2;
          function animate() {
            const dt = 1 / FPS;
            angle += Math.PI * dt * 0.1;
            
            renderer.clear({r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 0});
            
            renderer.render(mesh, {
              rotation: {x: uprightAngle , y: angle, z: 0},
              translation: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 11.0},
              scale: 3.0
            });
            
            requestAnimationFrame(animate); // Smoother than setTimeout
          }
          
          animate();
        
      } catch (error) {
        console.error('Error loading welcome model:', error);
      }
    }); 
  </script>
</BlogLayout>


<style>
  .about-canvas {
    width: 55%;
    height: 10%;
    display: block;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
</style>
